GIRLIE
That’s... disturbing. For a lot of
reasons.
CLARK
Right?! I fuckin’ pull over, right then,
turn around and tell the guy, “Ride’s
over, buddy, get the fuck outta my cab.”
Guy jumps out, don’t even pay.
After a beat, he beams at Girlie in the rearview-
CLARK
Didn’t even occur to you.
She simply shakes her head. Clark seems very pleased with
this stranger in the back, allowing himself to reveal a
vulnerable touch of melancholy.
CLARK
It’s just... weird, ya know? I mean. I
used to be exactly what you’d expect
behind the wheel of a New York City cab.
And now... I don’t know. I guess. Nothin’
stays the same no-more...
(a pensive beat)
And... I guess... it’s better that way.
For the most part. Can’t say I didn’t
have a good run.
Silence. Then-
CLARK
Nice you’re not on your phone. I mean,
